The paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and automatic curriculum generation for artificial agents, which are topics commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. The use of a setter-solver paradigm and the consideration of goal validity, feasibility, and coverage suggest a focus on robotics and control, which are covered in the sub-category of cs.RO. The use of 2D and 3D environments suggests a focus on computer vision, which is covered in the sub-category of cs.CV. Finally, the mention of guiding agents towards a desired goal distribution suggests a focus on system theory and control, which are covered in the sub-category of cs.SY.
